## Source of Truth

Before ANY change, read:

1. `/docs/features/map-chrome.md`
2. `/docs/features/_overview.md`

Use `Design.md` for connection card, details bar, right panel, layers dropdown, status gradient sections.

## Reusable Components

From `/docs/features/map-chrome.md` — Dependencies on Shared Code:

| Path | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `src/app/App.tsx` | `VpnStatus` type must match connection UI props |
| `src/imports/profile-icons/*` and other assets | As each file imports |

`RightVpnFeatures.tsx` / `MapLayers.tsx` define **`MapLayerOption`** used across `App`, `WorldMap`, and `layerData.ts`.

If a shared component covers 80%+ of the requirement, extend it via props/config. Do NOT fork it. Do NOT create a parallel version.

## Feature-Specific Constraints

- Figma-generated files: prefer minimal, targeted edits; avoid reshaping entire components unnecessarily.
- Adding a new `MapLayerOption` value requires coordinated updates to `App.tsx`, `layerData.ts`, `WorldMap.tsx`, and docs (`regulatory-data`, `map-chrome`).

## Patterns to Follow

- Default exports; inline styles for pixel-matched layout; props wired from `WorldMap.tsx`.

## What NOT to Do

- Do NOT duplicate `MapLayerOption` or layer lists — maintain a single definition in `RightVpnFeatures.tsx` / `MapLayers.tsx` per existing pattern.
- Do NOT create a parallel `src/shared/` UI layer — this repo uses `src/imports/` for Figma chrome.
- Do NOT add URL routes.
- Do NOT change `MapLayerOption` or `VpnStatus` shapes without updating `/docs/features/map-chrome.md`, `application-shell.md`, and `layerData.ts` / `shared-policies.mdc` as applicable.
